Q:

Quickly changing the text of a span with an image in it

I have a span with an image in it. When the user clicks a button, I want to change the text of that span to the text of a variable.
I've tried this:
var title = 'Hello';
$('#hello_button').click(function () {
    $('#hello_span').text(title);
});

But it doesn't work...

A:

The problem is because you're calling the function before the element is actually loaded.
You need to either bind to the click event or use the load event.
$('#hello_button').click(function () {
    $('#hello_span').text(title);
});

or
$('#hello_button').on('click', function() {
    $('#hello_span').text(title);
});

//OR
$('#hello_button').load(function() {
    $('#hello_span').text(title);
});

You can also use the jQuery load event as well:
//when an image is loaded
$('#hello_button').load(function() {
  //this is executed after the image is loaded
  $('#hello_span').text(title);
});

The load event is triggered when an image is finished loading, and is available on the document. 

