 swiss

As a Canadian I think the best way to comment on this is to say that we do not have Netflix on our cable subscription. We do have a Netflix streaming service that is similar to the one you are referring to. The basic premise is that you pay a few dollars per month and can watch as much streaming video as you want. There is a fee to access the most recent content and you also have to be connected to the internet to watch it. It is not exactly the same service that you are referring to but it is close enough that it does not really matter.

I think it is important to note that subscribers pay for Netflix and the streaming service is a secondary aspect of the service. The streaming service is included as a part of the subscription. It is not a separate service and is not billed as such. The streaming service is more of a value add to the customer.

I think I will take this opportunity to congratulate you for your excellent work on this blog. I really enjoy reading your posts.

@cdw I didn't know that Netflix had their own streaming service. Sounds like a good alternative to my mom who is a cable subscriber.

@shredder I'm so glad to hear that you like my blog. Thank you. I hope you'll continue to enjoy the content I post.

@cdw That's great to hear! I think you're right that Netflix streaming is a value add to the customer. I don't think of it as a "subscription" service.

@shredder I think Netflix streaming is a "subscription" service. It's part of the Netflix subscription. I was confusing the streaming service with the DVD service. Sorry about that.

