We would love to hear from you! Call, text, or email us using the form below and we will call you right back.Q:

Passing data to a child component

I have 3 components; 1 parent and 2 children.
Parent component has 2 components, one of which is a button.
I have a service that takes data from my parent component and passes it to my button component.
When I click my button I want to pass the data to my child component.
My parent component
import { Component, OnInit, Input } from '@angular/core';
import { UpdateStatusService } from '../services/update-status.service';

@Component({
  selector: 'app-update-status',
  templateUrl: './update-status.component.html',
  styleUrls: ['./update-status.component.css']
})
export class UpdateStatusComponent implements OnInit {

  public updateStatus: boolean;

  constructor(private _updateStatusService: UpdateStatusService) { }

  ngOnInit() {
    this._updateStatusService.getStatus().subscribe(
      (data) => this.updateStatus = data
    );
  }

}

My button component
import { Component, Input } from '@angular/core';
import { UpdateStatusComponent } from '../update-status.component';

