 the southern cone?

A:

I am not sure about this, but it might be because of the "Southern Cone" (aka "Cone of Fire" aka "Fire-Bird"), an event that happened around 6000 BC.
The name "Cone of Fire" is connected to the fact that at the time, the whole southern hemisphere was a lot closer.
The idea was to have a new civilization in the southern hemisphere, so the first settlers would be more advanced, and the whole southern hemisphere would have a new culture.
You can read about it in this book.
Up to now the southern hemisphere has more civilizations (Brazil, Argentina, Chile, Uruguay, Paraguay, etc.) than the northern hemisphere (United Kingdom, United States, Canada, Australia, etc.).
But the southern cone is the closest to the equator.
This is why the southern cone has the most advanced civilizations.

A:

As the other answers indicate, the answer is:

It's the Southern Cone

The southern hemisphere is the one with the most important and oldest cultures.

A:

Because at the time the southern hemisphere was the closest to the equator.
This is because the southern hemisphere was in a position to see most of the other hemisphere.
The northern hemisphere is the only one closer to the north pole.

